
[1]barley-water

   B'ARLEY-WATER, n. A decoction of barley, which is reputed soft and
   lubricating, and much used in medicine.

   French barley and pearl barley are used for making decoctions. These
   are made by separating the grain from its coat. The pearl barley is
   reduced to the size of a small shot.
